{
  "stem": "21349.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They showed us around London.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We hadn't seen London never.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they brought us to a hotel at East End in London.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And that was for the first time since 1933 that we had good food again and meat for the first time, because when Hitler came to power, one of the first things, besides other things, was to forbade-- he forbade [NON-ENGLISH], which means kosher slaughtering.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We came to-- we came to London.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we stayed in London over Shabbat 'til Sunday.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We went to the big synagogue which was nearby.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "There was a chief rabbi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "The synagogue was later burned out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And we went over the Tower Bridge.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We saw that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Next day, on Sunday, we went to Southampton.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And at 3 o'clock afternoon, we left Southampton in a boat by name of Alaunia, A-L-A-U-N-I-A, which was a 14,000-ton book-- boat, 10 times as big as the other.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] so we left Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was my father, my sister, and my two brothers, five people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "First of all, our trip was a very eventful trip, I must say.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because usually in summer, the boats go a little bit higher, because on the-- on the globe, you see, that's a shorter way to Canada.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we went too far up and we came into the section of the icebergs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And our boat had to stay-- stand still for about two or three days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We heard the foghorns all the time.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We couldn't go on deck.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Everything was closed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We saw fish, flying fish coming over the deck.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we-- we were actually standing in water until the fog subsided and we continued.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then we came to Labrador, to Newfoundland, and we came into the St.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
